<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2086">
Given an array of $n$ elements, your task is to divide into $k$ subarrays. The cost of each subarray is the square of the sum of the values in the subarray. What is the minimum total cost if you act optimally?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has two integers $n$ and $k$: the array elements and the number of subarrays. The array elements are numbered $1,2,\dots,n$.<br />
<br />
The second line has $n$ integers $x_1,x_2,\dots,x_n$: the contents of the array.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the minimum total cost.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le k \le n \le 3000$<br />
<li>$1 \le x_i \le 10^5$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>8 3<br />
2 3 1 2 2 3 4 1</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>110</code><br />
<br />
Explanation: An optimal solution is $[2,3,1]$, $[2,2,3]$, $[4,1]$, whose cost is $(2+3+1)^2+(2+2+3)^2+(4+1)^2=110$.    </div>
